        " «لاَ شَيْءَ عَلَيْهِ وَ لاَ يَتَوَضَّأُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.147 - Abdullah ibn Abi Ya'fur asked Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) about a man who urinates, performs ablution, then stands for prayer and finds wetness.\nImam (as) said: 'There is nothing upon him, and he does not need to perform ablution again.'."
        ]
      }
